#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "_rsnapshot_ is a very powerful backup utility that can be installed on any Linux-based machine. It can either back up a machine locally, or you can back up multiple machines, say servers for instance, from a single machine.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:27
#, no-wrap
msgid "_rsnapshot_ uses `rsync` and is written entirely in perl with no library dependencies, so there are no weird requirements for installation. In the case of Rocky Linux, you should generally be able to install _rnapshot_ by using the EPEL repository. After the initial release of Rocky Linux 9.0, there was a period of time when the EPEL did not contain the _rsnapshot_ package. That has since been rectified, but we have included a method of installing from source just in case this should happen again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:29
#, no-wrap
msgid "This documentation covers the installation of _rsnapshot_ on Rocky Linux only.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "=== \"EPEL Install\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:33
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ## Installing _rsnapshot_\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:35
#, no-wrap
msgid "    All commands shown here are called from the command-line on your server or workstation unless otherwise noted.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:37
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ### Installing The EPEL repository\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "    We need the EPEL software repository from Fedora to install _rsnapshot_. To install the repository, just use this command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:43
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    sudo dnf install epel-release\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:45
#, no-wrap
msgid "    The repository should now be active.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ### Install the _rsnapshot_ Package\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Next, install _rsnapshot_ and some other needed tools, which are probably already installed:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ``` \n"
"    sudo dnf install rsnapshot openssh-server rsync\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "    If there are any missing dependencies, those will show up and you simply need to answer the prompt to continue. For example:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    dnf install rsnapshot\n"
"    Last metadata expiration check: 0:00:16 ago on Mon Feb 22 00:12:45 2021.\n"
"    Dependencies resolved.\n"
