#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ## Installing _rsnapshot_ From Source\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Installing _rsnapshot_ from source is not difficult. It does come with a downside, however, in that if there is a new version released, it would require a fresh install from source to update the version, whereas the EPEL installation method would keep you up-to-date with a simple `dnf upgrade`. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:85
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ### Installing Development Tools and Downloading the Source\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "    As stated, the first step here is to install the 'Development Tools' group:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:91
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    dnf groupinstall 'Development Tools'\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:93
#, no-wrap
msgid "    You also need a few other packages:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:97
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    dnf install wget unzip rsync openssh-server\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:99
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Next we will need to download the source files from the GitHub repository. You can do this multiple ways, but the easiest in this case is probably just to download the ZIP file from the repository.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '    1. '
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "Go to https://github.com/rsnapshot/rsnapshot\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    2. Click on the Green \"Code\" button on the right\n"
"    ![Code](images/code.png)\n"
"    3. Right-click on the \"Download ZIP\" and copy the link location\n"
"    ![Zip](images/zip.png)\n"
"    4. Use `wget` or `curl` to download the copied link. Example:\n"
"    ```\n"
"    wget https://github.com/rsnapshot/rsnapshot/archive/refs/heads/master.zip\n"
"    ```\n"
"    5. Unzip the `master.zip` file\n"
"    ```\n"
"    unzip master.zip\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "    ### Building the Source\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Now that we've got everything on our machine, the next step is to build. When we unzipped the `master.zip` file, we ended up with an `rsnapshot-master` directory. We will need to change into this for our build procedure. Note that our build is using all of the package defaults, so if you want something else, you'll need to do a little investigation. Also, these steps are directly taken from the [GitHub Installation](https://github.com/rsnapshot/rsnapshot/blob/master/INSTALL.md) page:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    cd rsnapshot-master\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:123
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Run the `authogen.sh` script to generate the configure script:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:127
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    ./autogen.sh\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:129
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/apache-sites-enabled.md:20
#: ../src/docs/guides/web/nginx-multisite.md:42
#: ../src/docs/labs/sys_admin_1/lab7-software_management.md:485
#: ../src/docs/labs/sys_admin_1/lab7-software_management.md:718
#, no-wrap
msgid "    !!! tip\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "        You may get several lines that look like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        ```\n"
"        fatal: not a git repository (or any of the parent directories): .git\n"
"        ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:137
#, no-wrap
msgid "        These are not fatal.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Next, we need to run `configure` with the configuration directory set:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:143
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    ./configure --sysconfdir=/etc\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Finally, run `make install`:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:149
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    sudo make install\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/backup/rsnapshot_backup.md:151
#, no-wrap
msgid "    During all of this, the `rsnapshot.conf` file will be created as `rsnapshot.conf.default`. We need to copy this over to `rsnapshot.conf` and then edit it to fit what we need on our system.\n"
